Actress and choreographer Thembi Seete's fans showed her some love for Sunday evening  Mzansi's music talent show IdolsSA season 18. The 45-year-old received a lot of compliments about her good work on idols as one of the new judges alongside JR Bogopa, Somizi Mhlongo and rapper Proverb.  The show aired  Sunday on Mzansi Magic's channel 161 at 5:30pm. The actress wrote : "Tha time di nerve di reng mongwaneng. Thank you guys for your support,for encouraging messages." Thembi couldn't end showing gratitude as her fans has shown so much love for the incredible job. The musician said :" Sending lots of love guys episode one done and dusted." Also read: Big Xhosa wants to sondela Thembi Seete! She received lots of love from her celebrity friends and fans across Mzansi. Moshe Ndiki commented and said he smiled through out the whole show because of jer good work. "I love you,"he said. Bridget Nasinga said she did a great job. "You nailed it Nana,"she said. Thandolwethu wrote:"You're truely the coolest." A post shared by Thembi Seete ???? (@thembiseete_)  